==歷史==
[[File:Littlecolorado.jpg|thumb]]

小科羅拉多河附近的人類存在記錄可追溯到[[全新世|全新世]]早期。在[[納瓦霍人|納瓦霍人]]、[[阿帕契族|阿帕奇人]]和[[霍皮族|霍皮人]]入主該地區幷發展出灌溉農業之前之前，曾有不定居的狩獵-採集部落在這附近生活。<ref name="landusehistory">{{cite web
|url=http://cpluhna.nau.edu/Places/littlecolr.htm
|title=The Little Colorado River Basin in Arizona
|publisher=Land Use History of North America
|work=Land Use History of the Colorado Plateau
|date=
|accessdate=2010-10-17
|deadurl=yes
|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100926053819/http://cpluhna.nau.edu/Places/littlecolr.htm
|archivedate=2010-09-26
}}</ref> 西班牙的早期探險者可能是最早發現小科羅拉多河的歐洲人，他們將這條河流稱作“Colorado Chiquito”（即小科羅拉多）。<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://southwest.library.arizona.edu/azas/body.1_div.6.html
|title=Rivers of Arizona: Size, Extent, Etc.
|publisher=University of Arizona Library
|work=Books of the Southwest
|date=
|page=39
|accessdate=2010-01-17
|archive-date=2010-06-30
|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100630022549/http://southwest.library.arizona.edu/azas/body.1_div.6.html
|dead-url=no
}}</ref> 1853年-1854年，第一次有組織的開發小科羅拉多河流域的探險者由阿米爾·威克斯·惠普爾（Amiel Weeks Whipple）帶領著到達這裡，<ref>{{cite book | last = Worster | first = Donald | title = A River Running West: The Life of John Wesley Powell }}</ref> 他們的初衷是考察一條能夠建設跨洲鐵路的路線，同樣的考察活動之後又舉行了數次。在考察中，約瑟夫·C·艾維斯上尉（Joseph C. Ives）在其會出的當地地圖上標出了小科羅拉多河。<ref>also see Goetzmann, William H. "Army Exploration in the American West, 1803-1863," 1959.</ref>

1869年8月10日，[[約翰·威斯利·鮑威爾|約翰·威斯利·鮑威爾]]在[[鮑威爾的1869年地理探險|探險]]中看到了小科羅拉多河, <ref name="Powell">{{cite book
|last=Dolnick
|first=Edward
|title=Down the Great Unknown: John Wesley Powell's 1869 Journey of Discovery and Tragedy Through the Grand Canyon
|url=https://archive.org/details/downgreatunknown0000doln
|publisher=HarperCollins
|year=2002
|ISBN=0-06-095586-4
|page=[https://archive.org/details/downgreatunknown0000doln/page/234 234]
|accessdate=2010-01-17}}</ref> 他和他的隊員們探索了該河的部份地段。在日記中，他們將此河命名為“Flax River”（亞麻河，原因是[[河岸帶|河岸帶]]生滿了[[亞麻|亞麻]]。）<ref>{{cite web
|last=Euler
|first=Robert C.
|url=http://www.nps.gov/history/history/online_books/geology/publications/pp/670/sec2.htm
|title=The Archaeology of the Canyon Country
|publisher=U.S. Geological Survey
|work=Geological Survey Professional Paper 670: John Wesley Powell and the Anthropology of the Canyon Country
|date=2009-01-13
|accessdate=2010-01-17
|archive-date=2011-06-04
|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604200206/http://www.nps.gov/history/history/online_books/geology/publications/pp/670/sec2.htm
|dead-url=no
}}</ref> 和“Colorado Chiquito”，據估計他們可能在到達此地之前就知曉此處有一條河流了。<ref>{{cite book
|last=Powell
|first=John Wesley
|editor=Cooley, John
|title=Exploring the Colorado River: Firsthand Accounts by Powell and His Crew
|url=https://archive.org/details/exploringcolorad0000unse
|publisher=Courier Dover Publications
|year=2004
|pages=[https://archive.org/details/exploringcolorad0000unse/page/148 148]–150
|ISBN=0-486-43525-3
|accessdate=2010-01-17}}</ref>
{{cquote|它是一條令人厭煩的小溪，如此骯髒、泥濘，并散發著臭氣。大部份河段只有30至50碼寬，一個人可以踩著河底的岩石趟過去，而河水並不會淹至其膝蓋以上部份...其半數容積和2/3的重量都要算在淤泥上。它看起來就像是地獄的第一扇門。<ref name="Powell"/><br/>
—喬治·布蘭德利和傑克·薩姆納，1869年8月}}
不過這段描述並不是小科羅拉多河的常景，該河大多數時間內還是很清澈湛藍的——這種顏色來自於水中溶解的[[石灰華|石灰華]]和[[石灰岩|石灰岩]]。<ref name="Powell"/>

1870年代，[[摩門教徒|摩門教徒]]從[[鹽湖城|鹽湖城]]向南遷徙，并定居在小科羅拉多河的部份流域。<ref>{{cite book
|last=Abruzzi
|first=William S.
|title=Dam that river! Ecology and Mormon settlement in the Little Colorado River Basin
|url=https://archive.org/details/damthatriverecol0000abru
|publisher=University Press of America
|year=1993
|ISBN=0-8191-9126-4
|accessdate=2010-01-16
}}</ref> 在該河與普埃科河交匯處，他們建起了耶和華城和其他四城市，不過現在只有耶和華城還存在了。雖然有小科羅拉多河阻攔（雖然小科羅拉多河淺而緩，但是卻有[[流沙|流沙]]等嚴重威脅著移民的安全），前往此地的移民潮卻一直持續到1876年。<ref>''Dam that river! Ecology and Mormon settlement in the Little Colorado River Basin'', p. 20</ref>

摩門教徒從多次試圖在小科羅拉多河上建築水壩，以提供灌溉用水，但多數因河流流量的變幻無常而以失敗告終。<ref name="Abruzzi1">{{cite web
|last=Abruzzi
|first=William S.
|url=http://cpluhna.nau.edu/Research/ecology_and_mormon_colonization.htm
|title=Ecology and Mormon Colonization in the Little Colorado River Basin, Arizona
|publisher=Land Use History of North America
|work=Land Use History of the Colorado Plateau
|date=
|accessdate=2010-10-17
|deadurl=yes
|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110111012003/http://cpluhna.nau.edu/Research/ecology_and_mormon_colonization.htm
|archivedate=2011-01-11
}}</ref> 最終他們花費29年時間在耶和華城附近如願以償。<ref name="Abruzzi1"/><ref>{{cite web
 |last=Abruzzi 
 |first=William S. 
 |url=http://cpluhna.nau.edu/Research/grazinglitcolr.htm 
 |title=The social and ecological consequences of early cattle ranching in the Little Colorado River Basin 
 |publisher=Land Use History of North America 
 |work=Land Use History of the Colorado Plateau 
 |date= 
 |accessdate=2010-10-17 
 |deadurl=yes 
 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120302145245/http://cpluhna.nau.edu/Research/grazinglitcolr.htm 
 |archivedate=2012-03-02 
}}</ref> 此後不久，西班牙人開始從[[格蘭德河|格蘭德河]]地區向此地遷徙，并建起了聖約翰斯和孔喬。而來自新墨西哥州的美國人也建起了伊加和[[斯皮靈威爾_(亞利桑那州)|斯皮靈威爾]]。<ref>''Dam that river! Ecology and Mormon settlement in the Little Colorado River Basin'', p. 21</ref> 直到1960年代，摩門教徒依然是此地的主要居民，不過它們的獨立城鎮和農莊也最終被吸入亞利桑那州經濟發展的浪潮中了。<ref name="landusehistory"/>
===洩漏事故===
1979年7月16日，[[科麥奇石油公司|科麥奇石油公司]]的1億加侖含有铀尾礦的放射性水被排入小科羅拉多河支流普埃科河中，約1,100噸鈾礦殘渣污染了{{convert|250|acre|km2}}的土地，這些殘渣最終甚至流入了納瓦霍族保留地中。這次洩露的痕跡直到21世紀依然可以找到。<ref name=water>Brendan Giusti, Radiation Spill in Church Rock Still Haunts 30 Years Later, ''The Daily Times'' ([[Farmington,_New_Mexico|Farmington, New Mexico]]), July 16, 2009,  Section: Local</ref><ref>Carl Jensen, Project Censored (U.S.) [http://www.projectcensored.org/static/1979/1979-story6.htm 20 Years of Censored News] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100106050729/http://www.projectcensored.org/static/1979/1979-story6.htm |date=2010-01-06 }} Seven Stories Press, July 1, 2003, p. 84, ISBN 1-888363-52-5</ref>

